From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 20/20] winepulse: Reconnect DualSense mono speaker streams.

Spider-Man uses the DualSense one-channel controller speaker endpoint for
small sound effects separate from the main game mix. That endpoint can vanish
and reappear while the game keeps its existing audio client alive, for example
when the controller is unplugged and replugged, when switching between a
DualSense and DualSense Edge, or when the game starts before the controller is
connected.

Keep only one-channel DualSense render streams hotplug-tolerant. If the Pulse
stream is gone, keep the local audio client valid, find the currently active or
newly-added DualSense speaker sink, and reconnect the stream there. Update the
period bookkeeping only after a successful reconnect so failed reconnects keep
retrying from the existing timer path.

Some controller swaps do not produce a fresh PulseAudio render-device delta
because PipeWire keeps the split mono sink name stable. Refresh the mono
speaker stream once when a new non-silent effect burst starts so applications
that keep the original audio client alive still route effects to the currently
connected controller.

Normal game audio and the four-channel raw haptics path are unchanged.

